# This CITATION.cff lets GitHub auto-generate citation snippets.
# After the GEM 2026 proceedings publish, replace the placeholder DOI
# under `preferred-citation` with the real one.
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this software or the released LoRA adapters in academic
  work, please cite the GEM 2026 paper below.
title: "xdomain-ser: Cross-Domain SER Evaluation for Meaning-to-Text Generation"
version: 1.0.0
license: Apache-2.0
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Harrison
    given-names: Davan
    affiliation: University of California, Santa Cruz
    orcid: ""    # add when available
  - family-names: Walker
    given-names: Marilyn
    affiliation: University of California, Santa Cruz
abstract: >-
  A learned, cross-domain Slot Error Rate (SER) metric for evaluating
  meaning-to-text (M2T) generation. Combines a LoRA-fine-tuned
  Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct extractor with over-generate-and-rank, an
  NLI-based slot verification baseline, and per-example routing to
  reach 0.868 All-acc on the multi-domain test split.
keywords:
  - meaning-to-text generation
  - slot error rate
  - data-to-text
  - natural language generation
  - LoRA
  - LLM
  - evaluation metric
repository-code: "https://github.com/Vrindiesel/xdomain-ser"
url: "https://github.com/Vrindiesel/xdomain-ser"

preferred-citation:
  type: conference-paper
  title: "Cross-Domain Semantic Fidelity Evaluation for Meaning-to-Text Generation"
  authors:
    - family-names: Harrison
      given-names: Davan
      affiliation: University of California, Santa Cruz
    - family-names: Walker
      given-names: Marilyn
      affiliation: University of California, Santa Cruz
  conference:
    name: "Generation, Evaluation, and Metrics Workshop (GEM @ ACL 2026)"
